$ Python - os.path
@ os.path

{ Checking if a file or a directory exists #py-os-path-check-existence

  The `os.path` module has three functions that allow to check if a file and/or a directory exists:
    • `os.path.isfile()`
    • `os.path.isdir()`
    • `os.path.exists()`

